Identify a range of usability problems
with commonly used digital devices

Be aware of usability problems with
• PCs (including laptops/desktops/tablets/mobile devices)
• Digital cameras
• Cell phones (mobiles)
• Games consoles
• MP3 players
• Other commonly used digital devices (e.g. printers…)

Problems could include
• Difficult to handle/fiddly hardware
• Difficult to understand software
• Complex user interface
• Need to have lots of prior knowledge
• Specialist support needed to use device
• Each device is different to other similar devices (no standards)